R><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>w4nn4b3!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>3/31/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>6:32:13 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.allcanadiantrees.com/eq/Zapin.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Question for our wizzies on lanys...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">hmm, Melee damage looks a bit low, but even so, by chain casting draught line a Wizard should be able to out damage a couple tanks true (by a small margin - maybe 50HP per second if tanks are decent).  Does the ability to outdamage a couple tanks slightly by dumping a bar of mana on a mob make us the kings of damage....  Umm you decide. <br>
<br>
Draught line will not likely be used on Uber mobs so in that case tanks will be able to outdo us since even if we risk a smackdown by chaincasting lures on an Uber mob, we will likely be oom before end of fight and tanks will do all the remaining damage.  At end of fight, tanks can usually be healed quickly and cheaply ready to fight again.  There is no truly fast way to bring back a bar of mana.<br>
<br>
I like being a Wizard.  We do decent damage against most any mob.  It is possible for us not to do the most damage, but we have advantages that tanks do not, like the ability to solo for exp.  We do not have pets but we do have root and snare abilities, and a great ability to travel.  We can talk about things that can be done to make us more balanced, but we are definitely not the most difficult class to level.  Post 50 we still have some worth in raids and groups because of our Lure line and TP/evac/translocate abilities.  When wanting to be a better class, maybe we should ask ourselves if we would rather be a: <br>
Druid (post 50 reduced to same old kiting he has done since early levels or only valued in group for snare/harmony), <br>
Necros (solo or in post 50 group become mana batteries and summoners of corpses), <br>
Enchanter (hectic group action where you die and die again and very limited solo options), <br>
Shaman (buff the group, slow the mob the sit down - can solo but thanks to DoT nerf not as well anymore), <br>
Bards (hectic group work begging to cause carpal tunel syndrome), <br>
Ranger/Paladin (Sub-par tanks/poor healers/poor buffers - slow if any solo options),<br>
Cleric (med, heal, med - get asked for res - solo in right places but no faster exp than we can get) <br>
Shadow Knight (mediocre tanks with some solo capability), <br>
Mages (some decent DD but depends on pet and SoW to keep from dying since no root/snare ability - of limited use against high MR mobs)<br>
Monks (decent tanks, cant carry much and basically just sought after for good Pulling abilities)<br>
Warriors (Tanks dependant on others for exp and health)<br>
<br>
Every class has strengths and weaknesses.  Every class whines about their weaknesses and stays quiet about strenghths.  If we have any weakness it is our dependance on mana and the medding time to get spent mana back.  Are we useful in a group?  Yes.  Are we more useful or sought after than cleric, enchanter, shaman, Bard, etc.  Perhaps, perhaps not . . . most will agree with probably NOT.  Personally I think we are fun to play, can get in groups and raids when we want but can solo well when we choose also.  For those who don't like being a Wizard and think there is a better option, please change classes since everyone has different tastes and this class is not, nor should be, for everyone.<br>
<br>
Tanks/Wizards . . Apples/Oranges .. Is it really worth comparing the two?<br>
<br>
